notes: Start delayed 90 minutes due to rain. Match started at 4pm, reduced to 42 overs per side (2 bowlers to bowl a maximum of 9 overs each, 3 bowlers to bowl a maximum of 8 overs each), fielding restrictions lifted after 12 overs, interval between innings of 20 minutes.
West Indies innings: 50 from 49 balls, 43 minutes; 100 from 149 balls, 107 minutes; 150 from 192 balls, 134 minutes.

Vettori's best bowling figures in a One-Day International (previous: 4-49 v Zimbabwe at Hamilton in 1997-98).
New Zealand innings: 50 from 49 balls, 34 minutes; 100 from 108 balls, 76 minutes; 150 from 194 balls, 144 minutes.
